title: Nasir Hussain of PPPP wins PS-25 seat
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Candidate of Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians (PPPP) Nasir Hussain Shah Rizvi has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-25 Sukkur-IV constituency by securing 71,792 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Amir Bux of Jamiat Ulema-e-Islam Pakistan who bagged 25,059 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 41.54 per cent in the constituency.
